It&#39;s better to rely on `strDoubleList.size()`, and issue a warning or error, if the two values are not the same.

Use `CString::Replace` to replace characters directly, instead of copying to `std::string`. Also `std::string` has its own `replace` method as noted in comments.

Use `CComSafeArray&lt;double&gt;` to reduce chances of programming error.

Optionally, you can copy the result to `std::vector` to reduces chances of error. Then copy the vector to `pSafeArray`. This will ensure you have the correct array size.

